<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="DL4" checkit-title="Using Laplace Transforms to Solve IVPs">
  <statement>
      <p>
          Explain how to solve the following IVP.
      </p>
      <me>
          18 \, {y} - 72 \, \mathrm{u}\left(t - 2\right) = -2 \, {y''};\qquad
          y(0)=0,
          y'(0)=-3
      </me>
      <p>Hint: <m>\frac{1}{x^{3} + 9 \, x} = -\frac{x}{9 \, {\left(x^{2} + 9\right)}} + \frac{1}{9 \, x}</m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <me>
          \mathcal{L}\{y\}=-\frac{3}{s^{2} + 9} + \frac{36 \, e^{\left(-2 \, s\right)}}{{\left(s^{2} + 9\right)} s}
      </me>
      <me>
          {y} = -4 \, \cos\left(3 \, t - 6\right) \mathrm{u}\left(t - 2\right) - \sin\left(3 \, t\right) + 4 \, \mathrm{u}\left(t - 2\right)
      </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
